thread.title: M-R cross country lands three all-conference runners
thread.title_full: M-R cross country lands three all-conference runners

author: Jeff Holt
title: M-R cross country lands three all-conference runners
text: Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 7:32   20, 2015 at 7:32 PM With regionals on Saturday, the West Central Conference meet seemed more like a "tune up" for the local teams. Macomb freshman Maya Stovall took first place overall in the girls race with a winning time of 19 minutes, 28 seconds. "For the people who finished, compared to where we were three or four weeks ago when we were here, we were a lot quicker â€” boys and girls both," said Macomb coach Randy Ames. "I was really happy. We ran some great races today." Macomb senior Isabel Wohlstadter did not run on Tuesday in the girls race and then No. 2 runner Maggie Swanson had to drop out of the race on Tuesday because of asma. In the team standings, Liberty won both the boys and the girls races. M-R senior Dyesha Taylor (21:18) took 11th place overall in the girls race to earn conference honors. Riley Dulin (17:18) led at the 1-mile mark and finished third overall, while Kevin Jurado (18:11) also earned conference honors with an 11th place finish. Rounding out the M-R girls team were: 21-Jordan Copeland (22:34); 23-Arika Hofmann (23:02); 25-Kara Fisher (23:28); 31-Aunna Sheehan (24:25); 35-Grace Murk (25:19); 41-Claudia Garcia (26:51) and 44-Jozie Heikes (28:11). "They ran really well," said M-R coach Sam Marlow. "This course is tough and it doesn't allow you to go out and get a personal best record, but they held their own with what we had. We ran only four girls and 11 guys." About the three runners getting all-conference (Taylor, Dulin and Jurado), Marlow said, "They are peaking at the right time." M-R senior Trevor Blackman (19:18) also finished 20th, while Titan senior Gabe Brown (20:24) finished 34th overall. In the girls race, Liberty had four of the top-12 finishers to win it. Top-12 all-conference girls: 1-Maya Stovall (Mac., 19:28); 2-Carly Garnett (IW, 19:35); 3-Jacki Graham (Lib., 19:49); 4-Mariah Brodie (IW, 20:07); 5-Kaela Wellman (Lib., 20:13); 6-Megan Adams (Unity, 20:18); 7-Ella Borrowman (QND, 20:41); 8-Courtney Riley (Lib., 21:04); 9-Sarah Lewis (QND, 21:10); 10-Lindsay Ayo (QND, 21:11); 11-Dyesha Taylor (M-R, 21:18) and 12-Katelyn Obert (Lib., 21:20). Final girls team scores: 1-Liberty (41); 2-Quincy Notre Dame (60); 3-West Hancock (94); 4-Monmouth-Roseville (98); 5-Macomb (105) and 6-Illini West (111). Top-12 all-conference boys: 1-Lucas Booher (Lib., 16:55); 2-Dalton Ellingboe (WH, 17:02); 3-Riley Dulin (M-R, 17:18); 4-Reed Tate (Lib., 17:24); 5-Noah Pyles (Mac., 17:34); 6-Brady Cook (Lib., 17:40); 7-Logan Waid (Lib., 17:42); 8-Zach Zahnle (Mac., 17:46); 9-Carter Henry (QND, 17:51); 10-Dalton Melvin (IW, 18:10); 11-Kevin Jurado (M-R, 18:11) and 12-Alex Dranes (Mac., 18:15). Final boys team scores: 1-Liberty (33); 2-Macomb (47); 3-Quincy Notre Dame (80); 4-West Hancock (85) and 5-Illini West (105). By Jeff Holt
